indistinctly in the distance)

33:52.931 --> 33:57.603
ISAAC:
I... I...

33:57.636 --> 33:59.538
-Oh, my God.
-Look, look, I...

33:59.571 --> 34:01.273
I didn't do anything.
I didn't do anything.

34:01.307 --> 34:03.575
-She's 15! She's 15!
-I... I didn't do it.

34:03.609 --> 34:05.077
-I didn't do anything!
-Oh, my God!

34:05.111 --> 34:06.712
I didn't...
I didn't do anything.

34:06.745 --> 34:09.381
-Oh, God.
-No! No!

34:09.415 --> 34:11.417
-I didn't do anything.
I didn't do anything.
-No!

34:11.450 --> 34:13.185
-Oh! Oh!
-I did not. I swear to God.

34:13.219 --> 34:15.954
-I swear. I didn't do...
-Oh, no. Oh!

34:15.987 --> 34:18.524
-I didn't. Oh, my God.

34:18.557 --> 34:20.659
JOAN :
Oh!

34:57.095 --> 34:59.331
Okay.

35:04.303 --> 35:06.037
Okay.

35:08.307 --> 35:10.742
I think I understand.

35:10.776 --> 35:13.279
It's not about being alone,

35:13.312 --> 35:15.747
or about being in love.

35:15.781 --> 35:19.151
It's about the things
you survived.

35:19.185 --> 35:21.853
And as it's written,
"The world breaks everyone,

35:21.887 --> 35:24.990
"and afterward, some are strong

35:25.023 --> 35:28.260
at the broken places."

35:28.294 --> 35:30.429
-Go on.

35:30.462 --> 35:33.265
It's not the story
of a little girl

35:33.299 --> 35:35.934
whose mommy couldn't hug her...

35:35.967 --> 35:39.871
who grew up wishing a prince's
kiss could erase all her damage.

35:39.905 --> 35:41.673
It's about the damage itself,

35:41.707 --> 35:44.810
and how it makes us strong,
not weak.

35:44.843 --> 35:46.845
You survived the bullies

35:46.878 --> 35:49.014
and the way they made you feel.

35:49.047 --> 35:51.049
You cut yourself
with the dullest blade

35:51.082 --> 35:52.518
'cause it felt the worst--
I know that life,

35:52.551 --> 35:54.052
-'cause I lived it, too.
-I know.

35:54.085 --> 35:57.456
And then I met you,
and it was true love.

35:57.489 --> 36:00.192
Like in a fairy tale.

36:00.226 --> 36:02.294
This isn't a fairy tale.

36:03.529 --> 36:05.931
It is for me.

36:08.234 --> 36:11.102
Do you know what love is?

36:14.172 --> 36:16.675
It's a hot bath.

36:18.344 --> 36:21.012
What happens to things when you
leave them in a bath

36:21.046 --> 36:23.882
for too long?

36:23.915 --> 36:26.385
Huh?

36:28.053 --> 36:29.655
They get soft.

36:29.688 --> 36:32.023
Fall apart.

36:35.961 --> 36:39.097
I read that story collection.

36:39.130 --> 36:41.500
The one in your book.

36:41.533 --> 36:42.901
At first, I was confused,
you know--

36:42.934 --> 36:44.570
why is she carrying around
this sordid tale

36:44.603 --> 36:47.739
of sex clubs
and drug addicts and...

36:49.207 --> 36:51.443
And then I read this:

36:51.477 --> 36:54.846
"Junkies and masochists
and hookers,

36:54.880 --> 36:58.216
"and those who have
squandered everything

36:58.250 --> 37:01.453
are the ring of brightest angels
around heaven."

37:08.494 --> 37:12.130
It's a war, baby.

37:12.163 --> 37:15.267
This life.

37:15.301 --> 37:18.069
The things we endure.

37:19.405 --> 37:21.373
You said you saw the future,

37:21.407 --> 37:23.208
and it's an apocalypse.

37:23.241 --> 37:26.144
Who survives that--

37:26.177 --> 37:29.948
the lovers or the fighters?

37:32.117 --> 37:34.520
They sell us this lie that...

37:36.488 --> 37:40.158
...love's gonna save us.

37:40.191 --> 37:43.429
All it does
is make us stupid and weak.

37:46.097 --> 37:49.635
Thanks.
-Look at me.

37:49.668 --> 37:53.204
Love... isn't gonna save us.

37:55.774 --> 37:58.544
It's what we have to save.

38:00.346 --> 38:03.915
Pain makes us strong enough
to do it.

38:03.949 --> 38:05.584
All our scars,

38:05.617 --> 38:08.186
our anger, our despair--

38:08.219 --> 38:10.356
it's armor.

38:17.463 --> 38:21.266
Baby, God loves the sinners best

38:21.299 --> 38:25.036
'cause our fire burns bright,

38:25.070 --> 38:27.573
bright, bright.

38:31.042 --> 38:33.412
Burn with me.

38:54.265 --> 38:57.302
Okay...

38:57.335 --> 38:59.505
I'm ready.

39:48.286 --> 39:50.489
Is that...?

